<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title"><strong>S.E.C. Signals Tighter Rules Governing Treasury Bond Market</strong> <span class="divider"> | </span></span> Mary Jo White, the chairwoman of the Securities and Exchange Commission, said âit is essential that our collective regulation of this critical market keeps pace with dramatic changes in the Treasury market.â She added that high-frequency trading firms should be properly registered and regulated.<br /><span class="kicker"><a href="//www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/e0b81fc4-7760-11e5-933d-efcdc3c11c89.html?ftcamp=published_links%2Frss%2Fmarkets%2Ffeed%2F%2Fproduct#axzz3oyY7LSyS"> THE FINANCIAL TIMES </a></span></p>
